'''[[general]] [[formula]]'''
#{{chemistry}} the [[molecular formula]] of a [[class]] of [[compound]]s in which actual numbers are represented by ''x'', ''n'' etc., and [[organic]] [[radical]]s are represented as ''R<sub>n</sub>''
#:Example 1. The general formula for saturated aliphatic hydrocarbons is C<sub>n</sub>H<sub>2n+2</sub> and the molecular formula for propane is C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>8</sub>
#:Example 2. The general formula for alcohols is R-OH and the molecular formula for methanol is CH<sub>3</sub>-OH